!! Introduction
Every year we will take a Sunday to address a theme for the church. It has been now, 20 years here in San Diego. We are excited to see God's faithfulness.

It is easy to think about the sweetness of the old days. But that is not necessarily always the case. You meet so many pastors whose churches are falling apart or church are splitting because of doctrinal issues.

Church growth prayer: Desperately go to the Lord in prayer. Be thankful for people who are growing and being able to have people saved. Do not be complacent as the church rows. That is what a healthy body is. If you are a member of the church and you still don't know your fit is, unless every part is working and functioning, the whole body suffers.

One thing we ought to do as a growing church is to pray. We've had a year of suffering, going through difficult times at the church.

It becomes more imperative for you as members to grow together, to share together, and to disciple one another. We need to be praying. We need to be depending on God. As soon as we stopped praying, we've stopped as a ministry. If we don't pray individually and corporately, we have failed. Pray for your leaders.

Pray for success. Not the worldly kind of success. We want to be success for the Lord's eyes. Successful in our faithfulness to the Great Commission. Church is not meant to be a place where we come and follow the groove. But we come in as a part of the whole and be a blessing to the whole. We are to love one another. Our life should be a blessing to those around us.

